<div style="background-color:#00000000; margin:1em; padding:30px 40px; border:3px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 0px; text-align:center;">
It's been an immeasurable period since I've been stuck in that [[Level 6|abyssal labyrinth]]. For all I know, it could be as short as a mere minute, with nothing but darkness fumbling up my mind in a million different ways. However long I've spent in there though, it would be enough to me to leave me defenseless for my next encounter.

I was just walking, and then I stood on a trapdoor which could not support my weight, and I fell right through. My vision transformed from complete darkness to complete whiteness, distracting me from realizing that I was even falling. The sudden changes burned my eyes and my mind was running crazier than it ever had in that place, at least for a moment. The light settled down, and it just happened that I was in a really bright room. I looked up and saw the square-shaped black vent opening, which was how I even concluded that I fell from that place. 
</div>
<br><br><br>
<div style="font-size:72px; text-align:center; font-family:Optima;">Level 169: <span style="text-shadow: 3px 3px 0px #555555, 0em 0em 0.5em #DBD7D2, 0em 0em 0.5em #DBD7D2;">"Leeched Lighting"</span></div>
<br><br><br>
{{Class 1|hexagon=🕯|color-h=182|color-s=100%|color-l=76%|safety=Safe|security=Secure|entity=Surplus of Docile Entities}}
<div class="header">Description</div>
{{Blurimage|file=Lightlurkerfunction2.webp|caption=An image of '''Level 169'''.|width=390px}}
{{Blurimage|file=Loghallways.png|caption=A room with an entrance to a large Lightlurker-infested room.|width=390px}}
'''Level 169''' is an extensive complex of rooms linked by hallways and stairwells. All surfaces possess a pale, glossy shine, even those typically non-reflective, like paint and fiberglass. Additionally, numerous light fixtures dot the ceilings, providing ample lighting to the expanse combined with the reflective surfaces. When a wanderer initially enters '''Level 169''', especially from darker Backrooms levels like [[Level 6]] or [[Level 8]], their vision will appear bright white and have stinging sensations in the eyes, akin to a flash grenade's effects. The effects last two minutes, then gradually toning down to normal levels for five minutes.

'''Level 169'''<nowiki/>'s rooms and hallways integrate sophisticated layouts due to their bizarre and unpredictable shapes, mainly due to the inconsistency of floors on the level. For example, some floors may seemingly merge, some rooms can overlap floors akin to an atrium, and the height distance between floors varies considerably. While '''Level 169''' may extend indefinitely horizontally, its height extends 220 meters<ref>720 feet.</ref>, and wanderers first enter the level at the central floors. The color of lights in an area represents the altitude, in which lights in higher floors bear higher temperatures and cooler colors, and lights in lower floors exude lower temperatures and warmer colors.

Electronics that emit light, including flashlights and phones, fail to operate within '''Level 169'''. Continuous mishandling with any electrical systems, be it said handheld device or any of the lights, electrical panels, or power outlets in the level, will result in the object setting ablaze. Despite the lack of highly flammable objects in '''Level 169''', fire spreads rapidly and, when uncontrolled, can engulf an entire room in ten to fifteen minutes. Fortunately, one may find fire emergency boxes throughout the level, which use a sliding mechanism for easy access. The vents may quickly spread toxic air to nearby parts of the burning zone, where a blaze in one room can spread up to 100 meters<ref>330 feet.</ref> away.

Rarely, one may stumble upon a large, dark room on '''Level 169'''. These rooms may resemble ballrooms, empty office spaces, or function rooms. The lights in these rooms emanate a soft glow despite running at full power and lacking malfunction. This is due to these rooms housing communities of [[Entity 69|Lightlurkers]], with around 40-60 Lightlurkers per room. They typically stay packed close to each other, preferably close to light sources or near walls and corners. Despite the Lightlurker population in these rooms, the rooms' darkness hinders one's ability to see them, which may cause unnecessary contact, triggering a defensive reaction from the Lightlurkers. These dark rooms contain several valuable supplies, such as various foodstuffs, electronics, and even firearms, although they are difficult to obtain due to the room's darkness and concealment from Lightlurkers.

Some rooms of '''Level 169''' are decorated in a surplus of hanging ceiling lights and lamps, These areas, possessing polished wooden floors and countertops in haphazard placements, are known to feature several attributes to lighting stores in malls, such as varying light shapes and sizes. Some [[Entity 69|Lightlurkers]] reside in these rooms, sometimes tampering with the lights which may cause malfunction. These areas may have walk-in closets, housing a singular, extremely powerful light fixture. Due to the sheer amount of potential energy in the closets, they commonly contain ~4 Lightlurkers resting on the shelves. They are highly defensive over the light source, occasionally stinging wanderers when they feel threatened; a behavior unseen in Lightlurkers outside of these closets.

