<div class="header">Entities</div>
Mainly due to its surplus of light, '''Level 169''' is inhabited exclusively by [[Entity 69|Lightlurkers]]. They inhabit all areas of the level, with one Lightlurker every seven to ten rooms or hallways. They are prevalent in lighting stores, where small communities of 15-30 Lightlurkers inhabit.<ref>This number includes the Lightlurkers residing in the bright closet areas.</ref> Large darkened rooms boast the largest Lightlurker communities, boasting half a hundred Lightlurkers. '''Level 169''' has the highest Lightlurker population compared to other levels of the Backrooms, regarded by many as their hive, separate from [[The Hive|the level of the same name]].

While they are extremely rare, populations of [[Entity 36|Lighters]] exist in '''Level 169'''. Communities of the entity are clustered and they hunt prey in packs. Lighter temperature is dependent on altitude, thus encounters in higher areas of the level are more dangerous. The entity carries the potential to ignite any contacted surface. Lighters in '''Level 169''' fear Lightlurkers, which are impermeable to Lighter contact and can consume Lighters. 
<div class="header">Colonies and Outposts</div>
===<big><big><div style="font-family:Optima; text-shadow: 0 0 5px #848482, 0 0 8px #848482;">The Shining Lights</div></big></big>===
* Independent colony, founded by wanderers escaping from hazardous levels;
* Consists of 23 officials and ~250 members;
* Survival-based colony created from influx of wanderers escaping [[Level 6]] and [[Level 8]];
* Accepts nearly all members, providing essentials and housing;
* Major producer of crops due to their increased growth from the extra light in '''Level 169'''. 

{{Blurimage|file=Bigcomingsoon.jpg|caption=Elevators in '''Level 169'''.|width=390px}}
<div class="header">Entrances & Exits</div>
===<big><big><div style="font-family:Optima; text-shadow: 0 0 5px #848482, 0 0 8px #848482;">Entrances</div></big></big>===
*Trapdoors in dark levels, especially [[Level 6]] and [[Level 8]], can collapse when a wanderer stands on them, sending them to this level.
*Noclipping through the floor in [[Level 170]] will lead to this level if one initially entered through '''Level 169'''.
*Blinding oneself with light in [[Level 200]] will lead one here.
*Noclipping through heavy-duty electrical equipment in [[Level 107]] will lead one here.
===<big><big><div style="font-family:Optima; text-shadow: 0 0 5px #848482, 0 0 8px #848482;">Exits</div></big></big>===
*A black door leads one to [[Level 6]].
*A heavy, iron door sends one to [[Level 504]].
*Rarely, one may find a bicycle parked in the lighting store areas. Riding it will lead to [[Level 106]].
*Noclipping in areas with warmer lighting sends one to [[Level 198]].<ref>Usually around the lower 40-80 meters of '''Level 169'''.</ref>
*A white ladder leading to a black void in areas with cooler lighting sends one to [[Level 170]].<ref>Found only on the highest points of the level.</ref>
*Rarely, one may encounter a room with three to five elevators.<ref>These instances of Elevators are separate from [[Object 34]].</ref> Pressing UP sends one to any random one of the next 150 levels of the Backrooms, and vice versa.
